23:49.689 --> 23:51.038
Gives you that idea?

23:51.081 --> 23:53.040
Just a hunch.

23:53.083 --> 23:55.042
I didn'’t know Spartans
had hunches.

23:55.085 --> 23:57.174
Hunches win battles.

23:57.218 --> 24:00.003
From the age of 6,
I'’ve studied military strategy,

24:00.047 --> 24:01.875
from Sun Tzu
to Preston Cole.

24:01.918 --> 24:03.746
Riz speaks the languages
and dialects

24:03.790 --> 24:05.792
of every colonized planet.

24:05.835 --> 24:09.056
Vannak'’s battlefield discoveries
on the physics of plasma swords

24:09.099 --> 24:12.146
helped the Marines
develop stronger shielded vests.

24:13.930 --> 24:15.889
You see us as machines.

24:16.933 --> 24:18.805
But if you really want
to understand how we work,

24:18.848 --> 24:20.633
you'’re gonna have to dig
a little deeper.

24:20.676 --> 24:21.982
Wait!

24:23.200 --> 24:25.507
Any other tests, ma'’am?

24:30.686 --> 24:32.732
[door slides open]

24:32.775 --> 24:34.647
[footsteps recede]

24:41.131 --> 24:44.483
[heavy footsteps]

25:13.947 --> 25:15.557
Cortana?

25:15.601 --> 25:18.865
Can you show me what the house
used to look like?

25:18.908 --> 25:20.823
If I have enough
visual data,

25:20.867 --> 25:22.129
I can interpolate
and recreate

25:22.172 --> 25:24.087
a realistic facsimile
of the environment

25:24.131 --> 25:26.263
inside your heads-up display.

25:28.962 --> 25:30.224
Do it.

25:30.964 --> 25:33.009
[Halsey]
Just a word of warning.

25:33.053 --> 25:34.707
There'’s no telling
what kind of frightening

25:34.750 --> 25:37.579
and jumbled images might
emerge from your past.

25:37.623 --> 25:40.277
Remember, not
everything you recall

25:40.321 --> 25:42.628
is reflective
of real events.

25:42.671 --> 25:44.325
I understand.

25:44.368 --> 25:45.674
Okay.

25:52.159 --> 25:54.988
I'’m assembling
the visual data now.

26:04.737 --> 26:05.955
[John]
No.

26:05.999 --> 26:08.131
That table was over there.

26:27.716 --> 26:29.588
Dad'’s plant lab.

26:38.988 --> 26:41.208
Mom hung my drawings over here.

27:03.186 --> 27:04.884
My bedroom'’s this way.

27:04.927 --> 27:07.103
I remember.

27:07.147 --> 27:09.192
And what about in this room?

27:20.726 --> 27:22.771
[John]
Cortana...

27:22.815 --> 27:25.382
-I'’m not seeing it.
-[Cortana] I'’m sorry, John.

27:25.426 --> 27:27.733
I'’m afraid there's too much
destruction.

27:27.776 --> 27:29.430
I don'’t have enough data
on that space

27:29.473 --> 27:31.345
to make an accurate
representation.

27:31.388 --> 27:32.999
Perhaps if we go back
to the drawings, John.

27:33.042 --> 27:34.348
Hang on.

27:38.265 --> 27:40.354
[Young John, laughing]
Come on, Ellie.

27:42.008 --> 27:43.400
[giggling]

27:45.838 --> 27:47.404
Careful, Johnny!

27:47.448 --> 27:49.232
[laughing]

27:52.148 --> 27:53.280
[whispering]
Mom.

27:53.323 --> 27:55.151
[Father]
John, come here.

27:55.195 --> 27:56.457
Check this out.

28:02.245 --> 28:04.683
We'’re creating new life, John.

28:07.468 --> 28:08.730
Wow.

28:08.774 --> 28:12.821
And if the plants can live here,
then guess what?

28:12.865 --> 28:14.693
We can live here too.

28:17.434 --> 28:19.741
[Young John]
You smell like soap.

28:22.483 --> 28:26.443
[Mother] And you smell
like mud, goofball.

28:26.487 --> 28:28.054
Where were you
playing today, anyway?

28:28.097 --> 28:29.316
[Young John]
I don'’t know.

28:29.359 --> 28:32.101
-Just running around with Ellie.
-Yeah?

28:33.320 --> 28:34.495
Well, then I guess it'’s worth

28:34.538 --> 28:36.236
getting a little dirty for.

28:36.279 --> 28:37.890
Come on, let'’s get cleaned up
for dinner.

28:40.806 --> 28:42.416
[whines]

28:49.205 --> 28:51.338
Over here. Over here.

29:16.189 --> 29:17.756
[whispering]
What are you drawing?

29:26.503 --> 29:28.027
[Father]
Don'’t go too far, John.

29:28.070 --> 29:29.550
Be careful.

29:29.593 --> 29:31.421
Come on, Ellie.

29:39.908 --> 29:43.477
John, do you hear me?
I asked you what you'’re drawing.

29:49.875 --> 29:51.485
[whispering]
Can I see it?

30:07.240 --> 30:09.155
[barks]

30:09.198 --> 30:11.287
[Young John panting]

30:14.029 --> 30:15.465
[Ellie barks]

30:24.648 --> 30:25.606
[soft gasp]

30:52.198 --> 30:54.940
-Are you controlling this?
-I'’ve stopped projecting.

30:54.983 --> 30:57.072
Whatever he'’s seeing
isn'’t coming from me.

31:06.386 --> 31:07.996
[soft gasp]

31:09.215 --> 31:10.520
[Young John]
No, this one!

31:12.131 --> 31:13.959
[grunts]

31:15.221 --> 31:16.526
[barks]

31:24.752 --> 31:26.319
[Young John, laughing]
Heads.

31:26.362 --> 31:27.624
[coin being flicked]

31:32.020 --> 31:33.935
[birds tweeting]

31:39.419 --> 31:42.378
[Young Halsey] Correct again?
That'’s ten in a row.

31:42.422 --> 31:44.076
-Shall we try again?
-Yeah.

31:50.386 --> 31:51.605
Eagle up.

31:52.562 --> 31:53.737
[Halsey laughs]

31:53.781 --> 31:56.610
Well, aren'’t you
the lucky one?

31:58.612 --> 32:00.179
Do you know what I think?

32:02.094 --> 32:04.313
Actually, I think
I'’m the lucky one.

32:04.357 --> 32:06.185
Can I see you again?

32:06.228 --> 32:07.621
[Young John]
Sure.

32:07.664 --> 32:09.579
-Can it be our secret?
-Yes.

32:15.542 --> 32:17.718
[Halsey]
John, are you all right?

32:24.464 --> 32:26.596
[breathing heavily]

32:30.078 --> 32:32.472
[heavy footsteps]

32:40.262 --> 32:43.048
[machinery whirring]

32:49.706 --> 32:51.360
[Miranda]
That concludes testing

32:51.404 --> 32:53.101
on the three Spartans
and the artifact.

32:53.145 --> 32:56.539
Spartan 1-1-7 appears
to possess a unique quality

32:56.583 --> 32:58.454
not shared by the other
Spartans.

32:58.498 --> 33:00.456
Further testing,
perhaps on the level of DNA,

33:00.500 --> 33:02.241
will be needed in order
to determine--

33:02.284 --> 33:04.460
-[Kai] Oh, Riz, check this out.
-Whoa, whoa, Kai.

33:04.504 --> 33:06.549
It'’s my favorite
Covenant weapon.

33:06.593 --> 33:08.551
-Can you put that down, please?
-It'’s all right.

33:08.595 --> 33:10.162
See these holes
on the top plate?

33:10.205 --> 33:12.033
That'’s where the needle rounds
are primed.

33:12.077 --> 33:13.469
You pull the trigger,

33:13.513 --> 33:16.168
somehow they just know
how to target living tissue.

33:16.211 --> 33:18.170
[Vannak] As close as you get
to "fire and forget," ma'’am.

33:18.213 --> 33:19.693
[Kai] Soon as the needles
hit the target,

33:19.736 --> 33:22.304
they super-combine and bam,

33:22.348 --> 33:24.045
all you see
is a big pink mist

33:24.089 --> 33:26.526
of blood and evaporating
body fluids.

33:26.569 --> 33:28.745
-Massive damage.
-I know what a Needler is, Kai.

33:28.789 --> 33:31.052
Well, the Covenant
have another word for it.

33:31.096 --> 33:32.401
What is it again?

33:32.445 --> 33:34.534
-Qkhep'’os.
-[Kai] Oh, yeah, that'’s it.

33:34.577 --> 33:37.406
Qkhep'’os. Qkhep'os.

33:37.450 --> 33:38.581
[Vannak]
Correct.

33:38.625 --> 33:40.235
How-- How do you know that?

33:40.279 --> 33:42.150
[Kai] That'’s what they say
when we turn it on them.

33:42.194 --> 33:44.674
Though I guess
it could just mean,

33:44.718 --> 33:47.286
"Shit,
please don'’t kill me."

33:47.329 --> 33:48.765
Also correct.

33:48.809 --> 33:51.377
[Riz] Have you ever heard
a grunt beg for his life?

33:51.420 --> 33:52.726
[Vannak]
Pathetic.

33:53.683 --> 33:55.381
[Riz]
Kind of funny, actually.

33:55.424 --> 33:58.166
Oh, the Covenant
have the best tech.

33:58.210 --> 33:59.385
[Vannak]
No question.

33:59.428 --> 34:01.082
[computer chirps]

34:01.126 --> 34:04.129
[Kai] That Phantom we flew back
from Madrigal, that was unreal.

34:04.172 --> 34:07.262
Can you say that again?
The Covenant word for Needler.

34:07.306 --> 34:08.611
[Kai]
Qkhep'’os.

34:08.655 --> 34:10.178
[over recording]
Qkhep'’os.

34:10.222 --> 34:12.137
[chuckles]

34:14.182 --> 34:15.618
Of course.

34:15.662 --> 34:17.881
You Spartans have spent
more time with the Covenant

34:17.925 --> 34:19.666
than anyone.

34:20.667 --> 34:22.103
[Kai]
Ma'’am?

34:23.887 --> 34:26.281
What other Sangheili words
do you know?

34:33.506 --> 34:34.681
[Soren]
What the...?

34:34.724 --> 34:36.596
[distant indistinct shouting]

34:39.381 --> 34:41.166
Shit.

34:42.384 --> 34:45.083
Shit. Shit. Shit.

34:48.695 --> 34:50.349
What the hell are you doing?

34:50.392 --> 34:52.438
I'’m getting my ship
and going home.

34:52.481 --> 34:54.266
There'’s too many of them.

34:54.309 --> 34:55.919
Nah, there'’s just enough.

34:55.963 --> 34:57.486
You leave now,
you don'’t get paid.

34:57.530 --> 34:58.966
We had a deal.

34:59.009 --> 35:01.664
The deal was that I help you
find the resistance.

35:01.708 --> 35:02.926
We did that.

35:02.970 --> 35:04.667
They just got their asses
kicked by Vinsher,

35:04.711 --> 35:06.408
-thanks to you.
-No, no, no.

35:06.452 --> 35:07.670
There are people in Madrigal

35:07.714 --> 35:09.237
still loyal to
my dad, I know it!

35:09.281 --> 35:10.543
If we can get to them, I can
convince them to stand up--

35:10.586 --> 35:12.545
Kwan...

35:12.588 --> 35:14.677
no one'’s gonna step up.

35:14.721 --> 35:17.115
You need to face reality.

35:18.290 --> 35:20.553
There are no more heroes.

35:22.381 --> 35:23.556
My aunt.

35:23.599 --> 35:25.688
We need to see my aunt.

35:25.732 --> 35:28.865
She'’s the one who controls
the family money.

35:30.302 --> 35:31.651
I know where to find her.

35:31.694 --> 35:34.262
Has she got enough
to buy back my ship?

35:34.306 --> 35:35.655
Hmm?

35:35.698 --> 35:39.354
You leave now,
you go home with nothing.

35:40.747 --> 35:42.575
What kind of pirate are you?

35:43.489 --> 35:44.794
[scoffs]

35:55.979 --> 35:57.546
[Vinsher]
You'’re late.

35:57.590 --> 35:58.982
[blows]

35:59.026 --> 36:01.202
[Franco] My sister was late
to watch the kids.

36:02.725 --> 36:04.292
With what I pay you,

36:04.336 --> 36:06.903
you should invest
in proper childcare.

36:08.253 --> 36:09.297
Hello, Franco.

36:09.341 --> 36:10.907
You need me, Vinsher?

36:10.951 --> 36:12.692
Not me, my dear.

36:12.735 --> 36:15.216
The UNSC and the people
of Madrigal.

36:15.260 --> 36:17.479
Peace of our fair planet
is under threat

36:17.523 --> 36:19.307
by the arrival
of a troublemaker.

36:19.351 --> 36:20.743
An instigator.

36:20.787 --> 36:22.789
A rabble-rouser.

36:22.832 --> 36:27.533
I need her removed
before she rouses the rabble.

36:27.576 --> 36:29.187
Who?

36:31.276 --> 36:32.668
Kwan Ha.

36:33.582 --> 36:35.541
She'’s just a girl.

36:35.584 --> 36:38.370
Well, some girls grow up
to be trouble.

36:38.413 --> 36:40.981
She brought someone along
for protection.

36:42.548 --> 36:43.853
Soren.

36:45.420 --> 36:46.726
[Franco]
The pirate?

36:48.293 --> 36:49.816
He'’s nothing you can't handle.

36:51.426 --> 36:53.472
There'’s already
